Notebook[{
Cell["ExtendInfraSegment", "Title",ExpressionUUID->"2cee83bc-bce9-4f4b-bf5a-5354d07c79b4"],

Cell["[LLM Generated]", "Subtitle",ExpressionUUID->"83db8df3-dd48-46ca-af66-b3cf59a3149b"],

Cell["\<\
ExtendInfraSegment[g, segment] extends segment to a maximal line whose middle part \
is segment, returned as a List of unary InfraSegment[{line}] wrappers. \
Accepts a bare vertex sequence or an InfraSegment wrapper. Method (shared \
with FindInfraSegment) controls extension strategy. ExtendInfraSegment[g, a, b, c, d, \
n] is the Tarski synthetic-extension form (axiom A4 in finder shape): returns \
unary InfraPoint[{x}] wrappers for x with B(a, b, x) and d(b, x) == d(c, d).\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"e3896497-232e-43fa-8216-dc6d75ae1bda"],

Cell["Setup", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"e64085d1-513e-49b7-9e45-c209a01bcf1b"],

